defs.docs:
This crate provides wrappers around the underlying CoreFoundation
 types and functions that are available on Apple's operating systems.

defs.name: array
defs.docs: Heterogeneous immutable arrays.

defs.name: CFArray
defs.docs: A heterogeneous immutable array.

defs.name: from_copyable
defs.docs: Creates a new `CFArray` with the given elements, which must implement `Copy`.

defs.name: from_CFTypes
defs.docs: Creates a new `CFArray` with the given elements, which must be `CFType` objects.

defs.name: into_untyped
defs.docs:
Returns the same array, but with the type reset to void pointers.
 Equal to `to_untyped`, but is faster since it does not increment the retain count.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Iterates over the elements of this `CFArray`.

defs.name: get_unchecked
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, index: CFIndex) -> ItemRef<'a, T>

defs.name: get
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, index: CFIndex) -> Option<ItemRef<'a, T>>

defs.name: set_attribute
defs.value: fn <T> (&mut self, range: CFRange, name: CFStringRef, value: T) -> ()

defs.name: to_CFIndex
defs.docs:
Always use this method to construct a `CFIndex` value. It performs bounds checking to
 ensure the value is in range.

defs.name: CFType
defs.docs: Superclass of all Core Foundation objects.

defs.name: downcast
defs.docs:
Try to downcast the `CFType` to a subclass. Checking if the instance is the
 correct subclass happens at runtime and `None` is returned if it is not the correct type.
 Works similar to [`Box::downcast`] and [`CFPropertyList::downcast`].

defs.name: downcast_into
defs.docs: Similar to [`downcast`], but consumes self and can thus avoid touching the retain count.

defs.name: TCFType
defs.docs:
All Core Foundation types implement this trait. The associated type `Ref` specifies the
 associated Core Foundation type: e.g. for `CFType` this is `CFTypeRef`; for `CFArray` this is
 `CFArrayRef`.

defs.name: Ref
defs.docs: The reference type wrapped inside this type.

defs.name: as_concrete_TypeRef
defs.docs: Returns the object as its concrete TypeRef.

defs.name: wrap_under_create_rule
defs.docs:
Returns an instance of the object, wrapping the underlying `CFTypeRef` subclass. Use this
 when following Core Foundation's "Create Rule". The reference count is *not* bumped.

defs.name: type_id
defs.docs: Returns the type ID for this class.

defs.name: as_CFType
defs.docs: Returns the object as a wrapped `CFType`. The reference count is incremented by one.

defs.name: into_CFType
defs.docs:
Returns the object as a wrapped `CFType`. Consumes self and avoids changing the reference
 count.

defs.name: as_CFTypeRef
defs.docs: Returns the object as a raw `CFTypeRef`. The reference count is not adjusted.

defs.name: wrap_under_get_rule
defs.docs:
Returns an instance of the object, wrapping the underlying `CFTypeRef` subclass. Use this
 when following Core Foundation's "Get Rule". The reference count *is* bumped.

defs.name: retain_count
defs.docs:
Returns the reference count of the object. It is unwise to do anything other than test
 whether the return value of this method is greater than zero.

defs.name: type_of
defs.docs: Returns the type ID of this object.

defs.name: show
defs.docs: Writes a debugging version of this object on standard error.

defs.name: instance_of
defs.docs: Returns true if this value is an instance of another type.

defs.name: ItemRef
defs.docs: A reference to an element inside a container

defs.name: ItemMutRef
defs.docs: A reference to a mutable element inside a container

defs.name: FromMutVoid
defs.docs: A trait describing how to convert from the stored *mut c_void to the desired T

defs.name: FromVoid
defs.docs: A trait describing how to convert from the stored *const c_void to the desired T

defs.name: ToVoid
defs.docs: A trait describing how to convert from the stored *const c_void to the desired T

defs.name: boolean
defs.docs: A Boolean type.

defs.name: CFBoolean
defs.docs: A Boolean type.

defs.name: data
defs.docs: Core Foundation byte buffers.

defs.name: CFData
defs.docs: A byte buffer.

defs.name: bytes
defs.docs:
Returns a pointer to the underlying bytes in this data. Note that this byte buffer is
 read-only.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the length of this byte buffer.

defs.name: date
defs.docs: Core Foundation date objects.

defs.name: CFDate
defs.docs: A date.

defs.name: dictionary
defs.docs: Dictionaries of key-value pairs.

defs.name: to_mutable
defs.docs:
Returns a `CFMutableDictionary` pointing to the same underlying dictionary as this immutable one.
 This should only be used when the underlying dictionary is mutable.

defs.name: into_untyped
defs.docs:
Returns the same dictionary, but with the types reset to void pointers.
 Equal to `to_untyped`, but is faster since it does not increment the retain count.

defs.value: fn <'a, T> (&'a self, key: T) -> Option<ItemRef<'a, V>>

defs.docs: # Panics

defs.name: into_untyped
defs.docs:
Returns the same dictionary, but with the types reset to void pointers.
 Equal to `to_untyped`, but is faster since it does not increment the retain count.

defs.name: to_immutable
defs.docs: Returns a `CFDictionary` pointing to the same underlying dictionary as this mutable one.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: # Panics

defs.name: add
defs.docs: Adds the key-value pair to the dictionary if no such key already exist.

defs.name: replace

defs.docs: Replaces the value of the key in the dictionary.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes the value of the key from the dictionary.

defs.name: description

defs.docs: Create an instance of the superclass type [`CFPropertyList`] for this instance.

defs.name: into_CFPropertyList
defs.docs: Equal to [`to_CFPropertyList`], but consumes self and avoids changing the reference count.

defs.name: CFPropertyList
defs.docs:
A CFPropertyList struct. This is superclass to [`CFData`], [`CFString`], [`CFArray`],
 [`CFDictionary`], [`CFDate`], [`CFBoolean`], and [`CFNumber`].

defs.name: retain_count
defs.docs:
Returns the reference count of the object. It is unwise to do anything other than test
 whether the return value of this method is greater than zero.

defs.name: type_of
defs.docs:
Returns the type ID of this object. Will be one of CFData, CFString, CFArray, CFDictionary,
 CFDate, CFBoolean, or CFNumber.

defs.name: show
defs.docs: Writes a debugging version of this object on standard error.

defs.name: instance_of
defs.docs: Returns true if this value is an instance of another type.

defs.name: downcast
defs.docs:
Try to downcast the [`CFPropertyList`] to a subclass. Checking if the instance is the
 correct subclass happens at runtime and `None` is returned if it is not the correct type.
 Works similar to [`Box::downcast`] and [`CFType::downcast`].

defs.name: downcast_into
defs.docs: Similar to [`downcast`], but consumes self and can thus avoid touching the retain count.
